column1: #Text=25-130#Rolls-Royce Motor Cars Inc. said it expects its U.S. sales to remain steady at about 1,200 cars in 1990 .
#Text=131-190#The luxury auto maker last year sold 1,214 cars in the U.S.
#Text=191-274#BELL INDUSTRIES Inc. increased its quarterly to 10 cents from seven cents a share .
#Text=275-313#The new rate will be payable Feb. 15 .
#Text=314-346#A record date has n't been set .
#Text=347-444#Bell , based in Los Angeles , makes and distributes electronic , computer and building products .
